summary: SummaryThe MAC Locked Kiss Ink Lipstick is a flexible, breathable veil of full-coverage with a rich matte colour. A kissproof, transfer-proof and waterproof liquid lipstick with 24 hours of weightless wear.Finally, your lips are ready to drink it down, get it on and go all out, without ever touching it up.

reviews.headline: It is NOT long lasting
reviews.comments: I dont know how this product has so many good reviews. Like yes the colors are nice but thats it. This product did not stay on my lips at all and i just bought it. I did everything i did a lip scrub and hydrated my lips before putting it on and it was gone within 10 minutes of me leaving out the door. reviews.headline: Best Lipstick Ever
reviews.comments: This stuff really does stay on! And it doesnt get all crumbly or cracked after too long, it has a lightweight feel to it and literally lasts all day long. Sometimes I will reapply after a super greasy meal, but this is seriously the absolute best long wearing lipstick I've ever owned! Bought 2 different shades and wear them religiously. Soft and lightweight when dry and bold color. My favorite lipstick hands down!

reviews.headline: Product vs Applicant
reviews.comments:
I'm convinced a lot of reviewers have no idea what they're doing. I bought this after an artist put it on me in a store. When using it myself I got the same results. Lasts ALL day. For those sayng it didn't, I'm assuming they didn't let it dry OR they applied another product with it (gloss, lipstick, etc.) I'm now shopping for a third color. I only came to the reviews to see if there was a recent issue.
My only complaint is it's drying. That's not a big issue if you exfoliate and moisturize your lips at night though. Good luck everyone!

reviews.headline: Update - Locked Kiss Ink Lipstick
reviews.comments: I posted earlier with a pic of Upgraded with Stone lip liner. Here is a new pic 4 hours later AFTER eating at Benihanas… lipstick didn't budge. No transfer. No wearing off yet on waterline area of lips where most product breaks down and wears first. I'll update again later.

reviews.headline: So far so good - MAC typically doesn't disappoint
reviews.comments: Wearing Upgraded with Stone lipliner. Lipstick isn't sticky at all. It's weightless and feels silky but dries down. Not drying so far but the consistency isn't like a gloss. More like your natural lip with nothing on it. Will see if it lasts…

reviews.comments: This lip stays put!! Seriously the longest lasting lipstick I've ever owned!! Only down side is its a tad bit dry on the lips.

reviews.comments: I absolutely love this lipstick! I cam eat in it and wear it all day with little to no touch up! Its pretty comfortable on my lips and i can easily out chapstick on over it. I really hope they come out with more colors in this!! Maybe more cool tones??

reviews.headline: Favorite lipstick
reviews.comments: I absolutely love this lipstick! I cam eat in it and wear it all day with little to no touch up! Its pretty comfortable on my lips and i can easily out chapstick on over it. I really hope they come out with more colors in this!! Maybe more cool tones??

reviews.headline: She is a Vixen Superstar of her own Glam Story
reviews.comments: Well here we go again with an awesome review for a product that nearly  blew me out of the glam ballpark.  Are you ready?  Her name is Vixen and she is a super star goth superhero.  Stawwwp!  She lives on my pucker for about 4-8 hours and the compliments?  Endless!  Think about it lords and ladies, would you buy a creamy dreamy long lasting lip color that gets nothing but love stories?  Run to your nearest Ulta and get her now while she's still on the shelf.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I love MAC products especially their holy grail bullet lipsticks, which might have been the very first makeup product I've ever purchased back when I was a teenager! I love how long wearing they are and I was really excited to try this in exchange for my review as I've never tried a liquid lip from them! MAC's Locked Kiss Ink 24HR lip color is long wearing, pigmented and comes in a large array colors just like their bullet lipsticks. Its transfer proof, waterproof and kiss proof! I received the shade Decadence and it is a beautiful and versatile cool toned pink that you can play up with a few swipes as a natural tint or go full pigmented glam! It's a liquid lipstick with a big doe foot applicator that makes spreading the pigment fast and easy. The packaging is sturdy and compact, perfect for on the go and is your familiar silver reflective/minimalistic and sleek MAC look. 
It goes on thick like a cream and you might have to use multiple layers to get a fully opaque and pigmented lip. Once built up, it is highly highly pigmented and gorgeous! It feels very similar to NYX's soft matte cream lip but higher end and a much better quality! It dries down fast and doesn't sink into fine lines. It has a matte finish but is not drying at all. It feels nice and powdery on the lip once it dries down and it truly is kiss ink! I've tested it with my husband and dog and this baby never budged! 💋My husband was very happy that it didn't transfer on his lips and he can enjoy the color only on me lol. I went an entire day, eating and drinking and it did fade over time, not entirely lasting the promised 24 hrs but it is still a very long wear lip color (6+ hours). I would recommend popping it into your bag for reapplication throughout the day. I also loved how versatile it could be. I found that I could give one swipe and blend it all around my lips for a more natural lip tint look as well as using multiple layers to get an opaque dramatic glam look. Overall I would highly recommend!
faceoff_positive.headline: Beautiful kiss proof lips! 💋

faceoff_negative.comments: I will be honest and say this is not for me. I am very fair and it is an extremely deep, purplish red. It is beautiful, but not for me. I went through a liquid lipstick phase in my teens but I am more of a gloss/glossy balm/tinted balm person -- I prefer a natural finish. However, I think this would be a great choice for someone looking for a really comfortable liquid lipstick that is easy to apply. Liquid lipsticks can be difficult to apply without getting everywhere - I know from experience. I LOVE the applicator on this product - it is beautifully shaped to hug your lips. The formula is nice and liquidy without being drippy. This makes it easy to move product around and blend without being overly smudgy or sliding all over the place. It glides on very smooth with no chunks or buildup of any kind, and has that delicious vanilla scent that all Mac lip products tend to have. I do have one major critique: when I initially applied this, I noticed that the majority of the pigment/color was concentrated toward the outer edge of my lips, while the more moist inner areas of my top and bottom lips were a bit paler in comparison. Because the shade is so dark, this difference was glaringly apparent. I attempted to fix this with a second layer concentrated toward the inner part of my lips -- and even parted them and fanned to dry hoping this would reduce moisture and even out the color -- but the product would not stick and the weird gradient effect remained. I tried a couple more times but eventually gave up, because a product shouldn't really take this much tweaking to look normal. I docked a star and a half for that. Overall, this is a comfortable, pretty matte lip product with an inoffensive scent and pretty easy applicator.
faceoff_negative.headline: not for me, but a good matte liquid lipstick
